This is one of my favorite places to come for happy hour! When I need a stiff drink, and I mean a big one, I order one of the many liquors listed on Ceres' drink menu, usually with a soda on the side.  How the bartenders serve the liquor here is they fill a cocktail glass with ice and then pour the alcohol in until the glass is full. This ends up being a lot more than one serving's worth, but still at the price of one.  If you're not a liquor person, you can still order a draft beer, which comes in a tall glass. These are also pretty good prices, but I would like to see a better selection with fewer macro beers and more off the wall stuff.  As far as food, I enjoy the fried calamari or chicken wings. They are both consistently good quality and delicious.  I will be coming here well into the future as it's just below my office and I always need a drink after work.
